The paper discusses the task of question answering, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) research. The use of transfer learning and fine-grained supervision data is also a common theme in NLP research, particularly in the sub-fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of lexical and syntactic information, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
